  <div class="prose">
    <h1 id="dsh">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="lead" id="dsl">Your data is treated with confidentiality and used solely to deliver the service you requested. This policy explains what we collect, why, on what legal basis, and your rights under the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).</p>

    <h2 id="dsh1">1. Controller</h2>
    <p id="dsp1">Responsible for the processing of personal data within the meaning of Art. 4(7) GDPR is:<br><br>
    Daniel Fernandes<br>
    AlignedDocs<br>
    Contact: team@aligneddocs.com</p>

    <h2 id="dsh2">2. Data we collect</h2>
    <p id="dsp2">We collect only the information you actively provide through our order form: company details (name, industry, size, location), quality policy and objectives, process descriptions, contact person, and the email address to which we deliver the manual. We do not use tracking cookies, do not maintain user accounts, and do not run third-party analytics on this site.</p>

    <h2 id="dsh3">3. Purpose & legal basis</h2>
    <p id="dsp3">We process your data exclusively to fulfil your order and deliver the requested ISO 9001 quality manual. The legal basis is Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR — performance of a contract you have entered into with us. The email address is also used to contact you about your order, based on the same legal basis.</p>

    <h2 id="dsh4">4. Service providers & third countries</h2>
    <p id="dsp4">To produce your manual, your form data is processed by service providers acting on our instructions (Art. 28 GDPR processors). This includes our workflow infrastructure and an AI language model provider used to draft the content of your manual based on your inputs. The AI provider may be located outside the European Economic Area, including the United States. Transfers to third countries are protected by appropriate safeguards under Chapter V GDPR, such as the EU–U.S. Data Privacy Framework and EU Standard Contractual Clauses where applicable. We do not authorise these providers to use your data for their own purposes or for model training.</p>

    <h2 id="dsh5">5. Storage & retention</h2>
    <p id="dsp5">Your form data is retained for as long as needed to fulfil your order and to meet legal retention obligations (e.g. tax law, typically up to 10 years for invoicing data under German Commercial Code §257 HGB). Free-text content describing your business is deleted shortly after delivery once you have confirmed receipt of your manual, unless you ask us to keep it for revision purposes.</p>

    <h2 id="dsh6">6. Your rights</h2>
    <p id="dsp6">Under the GDPR, you have the right to access your data (Art. 15), have it corrected (Art. 16) or deleted (Art. 17), restrict its processing (Art. 18), object to processing (Art. 21), and request data portability (Art. 20). To exercise any of these rights, contact us at team@aligneddocs.com. You also have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority, in particular in the EU Member State where you live, work, or where you believe an infringement occurred.</p>

    <h2 id="dsh7">7. Data security</h2>
    <p id="dsp7">We use industry-standard technical and organisational measures to protect your data, including TLS encryption in transit and access controls on stored data. Access to your information is limited to what is necessary to deliver your manual.</p>

    <h2 id="dsh8">8. Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p id="dsp8">We may update this privacy policy to reflect changes in our service, legal requirements, or processor relationships. The current version is always available at this URL. Last updated: May 2026.</p>

    <div class="notice" id="dsn">This is a self-drafted policy intended as a starting point. For productive use in your jurisdiction, a qualified data protection lawyer should review and adapt it to your specific operational details.</div>
  </div>
